    "introduction": "Hailing from the heart of the Shenandoah Valley, Donna Winfield is a \"north of 45\" actor who deserves your attention.Part 1: The Leap In 1991, she did what she had always wanted-she arrived in NYC on a one-way bus ticket with $30 (okay, $10 after a questionable cab ride), a room in an SRO women's hotel. No backup plan, just a dream and relentless determination.Part 2: The Shift Fast forward 30 years-Donna Winfield isn't just continuing a journey. She's reintroducing and redefining. Bringing her screen presence, natural charisma, and commitment to craft, Donna proves that tenacity is the ultimate edge in an ever-evolving industry. She recently made her theatrical debut as Anna (u/s) in The Folger Theatre's upcoming A Room in the Castle, by Lauren Gunderson based on the women of Hamlet. Recent credits include The Equalizer (CBS), a feature film, TOW, based on Amanda Ogle's true story, \"Sins of the Bride\" (MarVista), and the SXSW award-winning TV pilot \"Marvin is Sorry.\"Donna Winfield isn't just working-she's leveling up. The best? It's still to come.",
